    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I ran with it enabled for a while, and yes, there are good reasons not to. Enabling mouse support captures mouse events in the terminal, so scrolling with the scroll wheel and selecting text with the mouse stop working while IPython is running. This may be dependent on the terminal emulator, but it happens on at least gnome-terminal and xterm.\n\nI think we should leave it disabled by default, so as not to break people's expectations of terminal interaction.\n"
  },
